    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5475" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κόσμος</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">order,
            arrangement</span>, then <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">ornaments</span> (of women),
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">trappings</span> (of horses); of building or construction,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἵππου</span> (the wooden), <i><span class="en">Od. 8.492</span></i>; freq. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κόσμῳ</span>, and (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εὖ</span>) <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κατὰ κόσμον</span>, both literally and figuratively,
          ‘duly,’ ‘becomingly,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 8.489</span></i>; also
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οὐ κατὰ κόσμον</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 20.181</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
